BROADBAND OUTAGE DETECTION ANALYSIS ¶

Project Objectives ¶

Broadband outage problem is one of the biggest problems now days. As we know that Broadband Operatores strive to provide the best possible service to customers and broadband outages are taken very seriously as they effect user experience and also impact the Business revenue.

Problem Statement ¶

The goal of this project is to " predict the outage duration " based on the reports filled by operators. Along with this, we will also discover important variables helpful in detecting outage duration. we are required to predict the outage duration (ranging from 0 to 2) for the test data. outage duration of 0 means 0 for no outage, 1 for short outages that last anywhere between a few minutes and a maximum of 2 hours, and 2 for long outages that can last from 2 hours to sometimes even a couple

Model Flowchart ¶

Introduction to the Dataset ¶

For the purpose of this project, we are considering There are 5 CSV files provided to us, they are described below:

A) Train Data

This data provides insights about unique event id for each observation of the outage_duration in a particular area_code

B) Broadband Data

This data provides details about the 10 different types of broadbands.

C) Outage Data

There are 5 different outage_type recorded in the dataset.

D) Report Data

This data contains log_report_type is a type of the recorded report generated by a technical team member after evaluating the outage. volume is the volume of data handled in the area at the time of report in custom company specific units

E) Server Data

This data contains the record of thetransit_server_type that is stored in the dataset. Transit Servers handle the requests and responses of the customers.

Prepare function for model building¶

In [450]:
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV,RandomizedSearchCV

def model_building(X, y, test, model, params = None, k = 1) :
    
    if params == None :
        model.fit(X, y)
        
        # return fitted model & train-test predictions
        return (model, model.predict(X), model.predict(test))
    
    else :
        model_cv = RandomizedSearchCV(model, param_distributions = params, cv = k)
        model_cv.fit(X, y)
        model = model_cv.best_estimator_
        print(model_cv.best_estimator_)
        
        
        # return and extra object for all cross validation operations
        return (model_cv, model, model.predict(X), model.predict(test))
In [451]:
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix 
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score 
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report 

def model_evaluation(y_train, pred_train, y_test, pred_test) :
    
    print('''
            =========================================
               CLASSIFICATION REPORT FOR TRAIN DATA
            =========================================''')
    print(classification_report(y_train, pred_train))
    
    print('''
            =========================================
               CLASSIFICATION REPORT FOR TEST DATA
            =========================================''')
    print(classification_report(y_test, pred_test))

for i in range(1,len(combined)) :
    
    if (combined.iloc[i].area_code == combined.iloc[i-1].area_code):
        combined.loc[i , 'area_order'] = (combined.iloc[i-1].area_order + 1)
        combined.loc[i , 'log_report_54_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].log_report_type_54 / combined.iloc[i-1].log_report_type_54)
        combined.loc[i , 'log_report_82_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].log_report_type_82 / combined.iloc[i-1].log_report_type_82)
        combined.loc[i , 'log_report_170_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].log_report_type_170 / combined.iloc[i-1].log_report_type_170)
        combined.loc[i , 'log_report_203_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].log_report_type_203 / combined.iloc[i-1].log_report_type_203)
        combined.loc[i , 'log_report_232_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].log_report_type_232 / combined.iloc[i-1].log_report_type_232)
        
        combined.loc[i , 'log_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].Total / combined.iloc[i-1].Total)
        combined.loc[i , 'unique_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].unique_n / combined.iloc[i-1].unique_n)
        combined.loc[i , 'server_type_11_prev'] = (combined.iloc[i].transit_server_type_11 / combined.iloc[i-1].transit_server_type_11)
        combined.loc[i , 'server_type_35_prev']= (combined.iloc[i].transit_server_type_35 / combined.iloc[i-1].transit_server_type_35)
        combined.loc[i , 'server_type_54_prev']= (combined.iloc[i].transit_server_type_54 / combined.iloc[i-1].transit_server_type_54)
        
        if (( combined.iloc[i-1].outage_duration != 'NA' )    &  ( combined.iloc[i-1].outage_duration != 0)):
            combined.loc[i , 'outage_before'] = combined.iloc[i-1].outage_duration
            
        if (( combined.iloc[i].outage_duration != 'NA' )    &  ( combined.iloc[i].outage_duration != 0)):
            combined.loc[i-1 , 'outage_after'] = combined.iloc[i].outage_duration

            combined.loc[i , 'area_order'] = 1

Conclusion ¶

Important Features ¶

a) In this Project ,I studied behaviour of outage and found following important features impactful in predicting outage type are following:

1) log_report_type_203( Importance: 0.031588%)

2) first_outage (Importance: 0.027785%)

3) outage_type_outage_type_1 (Importance: 0.024844%)

4) log_report_type_8 (Importance: 0.017116%)

5) log_report_type_140 (Importance: 0.014233%)

b) Removing thre features with importance less than 0.03 improve the F1 score by 1%.

c) order of id in log report file improved accuracy as well F1 macro average.

d) Other Feature engineering accounted for some degree of model improvment.

e) Averaging results from Xgboost and Random Forest gave a better approximation of population data it seems.

f) Add new features , feature importance and tuning hyperparameters further

g) We can check our model performance by AUC & ROC curve because AUC & ROC performs very well in multiclass data.

h) AUC is useful metric even when class are highly unbalanced.

Model Performance ¶

Based on business requirement,Feature importance threshold can be set on differet parameters.This threshold can be varied for different performance of these models.Recall and Precision tradeoff is entirely based on business decision.

Our models consistentently performed with ~0.80 F1 macro avg.

Model Improvement ¶

Based on the above model performance ,there is a scope in improving model performance by :

1) Adding more outage data to the training dataset help in predicting unseen outage behaviour time to time.

2) Ensembling methods with hyperparameter tuning can improve performance of the models.

3) Above model will help in predicting outage type ,which will be helpful for Broadband companies to improve business thoroughly.

4) Further improvement in the project will help Company to take decision against most prone outage area and will help to resolve in this domain.

5) Perform Neural Network modeling to get better approximations of non-linearity

6) Perform Dimensionality reduction to reduce multicollinearity.

7) Perform unsupervised learning to look if there are id's in the neighborhood of id's of train data.

8) Try different transformations on Volume and bin id's into different categories.

The End
